### Test Rate Limiting Fix
### This file tests the /api/analyze endpoint with a sample PDF
### Use REST Client extension in VS Code or curl

### 1. Test with a sample PDF file
POST http://localhost:3000/api/analyze
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="test.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./test-deck.pdf
------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW--

### Expected behavior:
### - NLU analysis runs sequentially (one slide at a time with 500ms delay)
### - Granite scoring runs sequentially (one slide at a time with 500ms delay)
### - No 429 "Too Many Requests" errors in logs
### - Total time: ~16 seconds for 16 slides (8s NLU + 8s Granite)
### - Check .bob/log.md for confirmation

### 2. Alternative: Use curl command
### Run this in terminal:
### curl -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/analyze \
###   -F "file=@./test-deck.pdf" \
###   -H "Content-Type: multipart/form-data"